## Bug Report

<!-- Thanks for your bug report! Don't worry if you can't fill out all the sections. -->
This portion [here](https://github.com/tikv/tikv/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#building-and-testing) says:
> You can run the test suite alone, or just run a specific test:
```
# Run the full suite
make test
# Run a specific test
cargo test $TESTNAME
```

<!-- You can run `tikv-server --version` -->

commit 15082b6cb7d1be3414badc0b74a21b67a505a29e (HEAD -> master, origin/master, origin/HEAD)

### Steps to reproduce
<!-- If possible, provide a recipe for reproducing the error. A complete runnable program is good. -->

`$ time RUSTFLAGS=-Cdebuginfo=2 cargo test test_batch`
OR
`$ time RUSTFLAGS=-Cdebuginfo=2 cargo test raftstore::store::fsm::batch::tests::test_batch`

### What did you expect?
To see that `test_batch` test being ran, which is [the only one](https://github.com/tikv/tikv/issues/4102) that fails during `make test`.

### What did happened?
nothing, therefore I can conclude that `cargo test $TESTNAME` isn't the way to run a specific test, anymore.
